data.chText: 风帽，兜帽（外衣的一部分，可拉起蒙住头颈）
data.enText: a part of a coat, etc. that you can pull up to cover the back and top of your head
a jacket with a detachable hood
a piece of cloth put over sb's face and head so that they cannot be recognized or so that they cannot see

data.chText: 学位连领帽（表示学位种类）
data.enText: a piece of coloured silk or fur worn over an academic gown to show the kind of degree held by the person wearing it
a folding cover over a car, etc.

data.chText: 我们一路上敞着车篷开车。
data.enText: We drove all the way with the hood down.
a cover placed over a device or machine, for example, to protect it
an extractor hood (= one that removes cooking smells from a kitchen)
a neighbourhood, especially a person's own neighbourhood

tr: a headdress that protects the head and face
the folding roof of a carriage

value.def: A hood is a part of a coat which you can pull up to cover your head. It is in the shape of a triangular bag attached to the neck of the coat at the back.
A hood is a bag made of cloth, which is put over someone's head and face so that they cannot be recognized or so that they cannot see.
The hood of a car is the metal cover over the engine at the front.

value.boxr_value: in BRIT, use 英国英语用 bonnet

value.def: A hood is a covering on a vehicle or a piece of equipment, which is usually curved and can be removed.

example.ex: Why aren't all lenses supplied with a lens hood?
example.tran: 为什么不给所有的镜头都配上遮光罩呢？

value.tran: 折叠式车篷;（设备上的）罩，防护罩

value.def: A cooker hood is an electrical device fitted over a cooker above head height, and containing an extractor fan and usually a light.
